# Network identifier risk model

The system materially reduces misuse risk while preserving emergency evidentiary value.

Normal MVP behavior:
- no raw MAC/BSSID/BLE identifiers in normal UI
- no open search or lookup by identifier
- store `idHash` for mock wireless observations/devices
- model nullable `rawIdProtected` as internal-only protected data
- never display `rawIdProtected`
- keep normal snapshot retention short
- require verified emergency/legal workflow before raw export
- audit all emergency/export access

Future real OS-permitted wireless identifiers must pass through salted hashing, protected local storage, retention, and audit controls before storage or display.

